+# Releasing InkFrame Studio
+
+Debug APK, GitHub Releases only. No Play Store signing.
+
+App identity:
+
+| | |
+|---|---|
+| Application ID | `com.inkframe.studio` |
+| Min / Target SDK | 26 / 35 |
+| Artifact | **debug APK** – `app-debug.apk` |
+| Version source | `web/metadata.json` |
+
+---
+
+## Release – 3 commands
+
+```bash
+# 1. Bump version
+./inkframe-cli bump patch   # or minor / major
+# updates web/metadata.json + package.json, regenerates RELEASE_NOTES.md
+
+# 2. Verify
+./inkframe-cli release-check
+# prints the exact git tag / push commands
+
+# 3. Tag & push
+git add -A && git commit -m "v0.x.y"
+git tag v0.x.y
+git push origin main --tags
+```
+
+CI (`.github/workflows/release.yml`) then:
+1. Runs unit tests
+2. Builds debug APK (`:app:assembleDebug`)
+3. Publishes `InkFrame-v0.x.y-debug.apk` to GitHub Releases
+
+That's it. The APK is fully wrapped, offline, sideload-ready.
+
+---
+
+## Manual APK build
+
+```bash
+./inkframe-cli build-apk
+# app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk
+```
+
+Install:
+```bash
+adb install -r app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk
+```
+
+---
+
+## Smoke test checklist
+
+See [`RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md`](RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md) – backup archive → install APK → verify brush / stylus / export GIF / video.
+
+---
+
+## Versioning
+
+- Marketing version: `web/metadata.json` → `"version": "0.x.y"`
+- Bump helper: `node tools/bump-version.mjs patch|minor|major`
+- `versionCode` in `app/build.gradle.kts` – auto-increments in CI via `GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER`, stays at base locally.
+- Override: `INKFRAME_VERSION_CODE=42 ./gradlew :app:assembleDebug`
+
+Release notes are generated from `CHANGELOG.md` + `web/metadata.json`:
+```
+node tools/update-release-notes.mjs
+```
+
+---
+
+## Agent Mode / CI
+
+Trigger a build without pushing a tag:
+
+```bash
+gh workflow run agent-build.yml -f task=apk
+gh run watch
+gh run download -n inkframe-agent-apk
+```
+
+See `.github/workflows/agent-build.yml` and [`PIPELINE.md`](PIPELINE.md).
